  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(2) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Then David the king stood up upon his feet.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—To address the assembly, the king naturally rose from his throne.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Hear me.—Calling attention, as in Genesis 23:11-15.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Hear me.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Calling attention, as in ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Genesis 23:11-15",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "My brethren, and my people.—Comp. 1Samuel 30:23; 2Samuel 19:12. The words do not so much imply condescension as an acknowledgment of what every one of David’s hearers felt to be true—viz., that all Israel were kin, and David the head of the family.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "My brethren, and my people.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Comp. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Samuel 30:23",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2Samuel 19:12",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". The words do not so much imply condescension as an acknowledgment of what every one of David’s hearers felt to be true—viz., that all Israel were kin, and David the head of the family.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "As for me, I had in mine heart to build.—See 1Chronicles 22:7-8 and the Notes there. 1Chronicles 28:2-7 of this chapter are in substance, and partly in expression, identical with 1Chronicles 22:7-10 (David’s private charge to Solomon).",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "As for me, I had in mine heart to build.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—See ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Chronicles 22:7-8",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " and the Notes there. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Chronicles 28:2-7",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " of this chapter are in substance, and partly in expression, identical with ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Chronicles 22:7-10",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " (David’s private charge to Solomon).",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "An house of rest—i.e., a permanent abode instead of a sacred tent, which gave the idea of wandering from place to place, like the nomads of the desert. (Comp. Psalm 132:8.)",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "An house of rest",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "i.e.,",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " a permanent abode instead of a sacred tent, which gave the idea of wandering from place to place, like the nomads of the desert. (Comp. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Psalm 132:8",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ".)",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The footstool of our God.—The so-called mercy-seat, the golden kappôreth suspended over the Ark, on which were the cherubim—the throne of Deity (Psalm 99:1).",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "The footstool of our God.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—The so-called mercy-seat, the golden ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "kappôreth",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " suspended over the Ark, on which were the cherubim—the throne of Deity (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Psalm 99:1",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ").",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And had made ready.—Rather, and I made ready, by amassing stores of material (1Chronicles 22:2-4; 1Chronicles 22:14-16).",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "And had made ready.",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "—Rather, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "and I made ready,",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " by amassing stores of material (",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Chronicles 22:2-4",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1Chronicles 22:14-16",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ").",
            "children": []
