  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 28:2",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "1 Chronicles 28:2",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Then the king stood up upon his feet — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Out of reverence to God, and respect to this great and honourable assembly. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And said, Hear me, my brethren — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "So he calls the princes and chief rulers, both because they had a share with him, though under him, in the government; and in compliance with the divine command, that ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the king ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "should ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "not be lifted up above his brethren, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Deuteronomy 17:20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "A house of rest — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "A place where it might be fixed, and no more removed from place to place, as it had been. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "For the footstool — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "A house for the ark is here styled, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "a house for the footstool of our God. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Heaven is his throne: the earth and the most magnificent temples thereon are but his footstool. So much difference is there between the manifestations of his glory, in the upper and in the lower world!",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
